  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "RESIDENT TECHNICAL OFFICER",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Supervise and monitor site works in accordance with approved drawings, specifications, and contract requirements</p></li><li><p>Ensure construction works comply with BCA regulations, codes of practice, and project quality standards</p></li><li><p>Inspect workmanship and materials used on site</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with consultants, contractors, and site personnel on technical matters</p></li><li><p>Attend site meetings and prepare inspection records and reports</p></li><li><p>Identify and report non-conformance, site issues, and deviations to the Qualified Person</p></li><li><p>Ensure proper documentation and records are maintained</p></li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Degree in Civil Engineering, Structural Engineering, or related discipline</p></li><li><p>Registered with the Building and Construction Authority (BCA) as a Resident Technical Officer (RTO)</p></li><li><p>Minimum 3 years of relevant site supervision experience (viaduct structures, MRT projects or road works)</p></li><li><p>Able to work independently and stationed full-time on site</p></li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 3,
